{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'd like to do pretty much what I did the first time,"},{"time":3000,"text":"which is to choose a light-hearted theme."},{"time":6000,"text":"Last time, I talked about death and dying."},{"time":9000,"text":"This time, I'm going to talk about mental illness."},{"time":14000,"text":"But it has to be technological,"},{"time":15000,"text":"so I'll talk about electroshock therapy. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20000,"text":"You know, ever since man had any notion"},{"time":23000,"text":"that some of his other people, his colleagues,"},{"time":27000,"text":"could be different, could be strange, could be severely depressed"},{"time":31000,"text":"or what we now recognize as schizophrenia,"},{"time":35000,"text":"he was certain that this kind of illness"},{"time":38000,"text":"had to come from evil spirits getting into the body."},{"time":41000,"text":"So, the way of treating these diseases"},{"time":43000,"text":"in early times was to, in some way or other,"},{"time":46000,"text":"exorcise those evil spirits, and this is still going on, as you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"But it wasn't enough to use the priests."},{"time":53000,"text":"When medicine became somewhat scientific, in about 450 BC,"},{"time":58000,"text":"with Hippocrates and those boys,"},{"time":60000,"text":"they tried to look for herbs, plants"},{"time":64000,"text":"that would literally shake the bad spirits out."},{"time":67000,"text":"So, they found certain plants that could cause convulsions."},{"time":70000,"text":"And the herbals, the botanical books of up to the late Middle Ages,"},{"time":76000,"text":"the Renaissance are filled with prescriptions"},{"time":80000,"text":"for causing convulsions to shake the evil spirits out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"Finally, in about the sixteenth century,"},{"time":89000,"text":"a physician whose name was Theophrastus Bombastus Aureolus von Hohenheim,"},{"time":95000,"text":"called Paracelsus, a name probably familiar to some people here --"},{"time":99000,"text":"(Laughter) -- good, old Paracelsus"},{"time":104000,"text":"found that he could predict the degree of convulsion"},{"time":108000,"text":"by using a measured amount of camphor to produce the convulsion."},{"time":112000,"text":"Can you imagine going to your closet, pulling out a mothball, and"},{"time":115000,"text":"chewing on it if you're feeling depressed?"},{"time":118000,"text":"It's better than Prozac, but I wouldn't recommend it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"So what we see in the seventeenth, eighteenth century"},{"time":124000,"text":"is the continued search for medications other than camphor that'll do the trick."},{"time":129000,"text":"Well, along comes Benjamin Franklin,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and he comes close to convulsing himself"},{"time":133000,"text":"with a bolt of electricity off the end of his kite."},{"time":137000,"text":"And so people begin thinking in terms of electricity to produce convulsions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"And then, we fast-forward to about 1932,"},{"time":146000,"text":"when three Italian psychiatrists, who were largely treating depression,"},{"time":152000,"text":"began to notice among their patients, who were also epileptics,"},{"time":155000,"text":"that if they had an epileptic -- a series of epileptic fits,"},{"time":158000,"text":"a lot of them in a row -- the depression would very frequently lift."},{"time":162000,"text":"Not only would it lift, but it might never return."},{"time":166000,"text":"So they got very interested in producing convulsions,"},{"time":171000,"text":"measured types of convulsions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"And they thought, \"Well, we've got electricity, we'll plug somebody into the wall."},{"time":176000,"text":"That always makes hair stand up and people shake a lot.\""},{"time":179000,"text":"So, they tried it on a few pigs, and none of the pigs were killed."},{"time":183000,"text":"So, they went to the police and they said,"},{"time":185000,"text":"\"We know that at the Rome railroad station,"},{"time":188000,"text":"there are all these lost souls wandering around,"},{"time":190000,"text":"muttering gibberish. Can you bring one of them to us?\""},{"time":194000,"text":"Someone who is, as the Italians say, \"cagoots.\""},{"time":197000,"text":"So they found this \"cagoots\" guy,"},{"time":199000,"text":"a 39-year-old man who was really hopelessly schizophrenic,"},{"time":202000,"text":"who was known, had been known for months,"},{"time":205000,"text":"to be literally defecating on himself,"},{"time":209000,"text":"talking nothing that made any sense,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and they brought him into the hospital."},{"time":213000,"text":"So these three psychiatrists, after about two or three weeks of observation,"},{"time":217000,"text":"laid him down on a table,"},{"time":219000,"text":"connected his temples to a very small source of current."},{"time":224000,"text":"They thought, \"Well, we'll try 55 volts, two-tenths of a second."},{"time":228000,"text":"That's not going to do anything terrible to him.\""},{"time":231000,"text":"So they did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"Well, I have the following from a firsthand observer,"},{"time":236000,"text":"who told me this about 35 years ago,"},{"time":239000,"text":"when I was thinking about these things"},{"time":241000,"text":"for some research project of mine."},{"time":244000,"text":"He said, \"This fellow\" -- remember, he wasn't even put to sleep --"},{"time":248000,"text":"\"after this major grand mal convulsion,"},{"time":250000,"text":"sat right up, looked at these three fellas and said,"},{"time":253000,"text":"'What the fuck are you assholes trying to do?' \""},{"time":257000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":265000,"text":"If I could only say that in Italian."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"Well, they were happy as could be, because he"},{"time":271000,"text":"hadn't said a rational word in the weeks of observation."},{"time":275000,"text":"So they plugged him in again,"},{"time":280000,"text":"and this time they used 110 volts for half a second."},{"time":284000,"text":"And to their amazement, after it was over,"},{"time":287000,"text":"he began speaking like he was perfectly well."},{"time":290000,"text":"He relapsed a little bit, they gave him a series of treatments,"},{"time":293000,"text":"and he was essentially cured."},{"time":294000,"text":"But of course, having schizophrenia,"},{"time":297000,"text":"within a few months, it returned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"But they wrote a paper about this,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and everybody in the Western world began using electricity"},{"time":306000,"text":"to convulse people who were either schizophrenic or severely depressed."},{"time":310000,"text":"It didn't work very well on the schizophrenics,"},{"time":312000,"text":"but it was pretty clear in the '30s and by the middle of the '40s"},{"time":315000,"text":"that electroconvulsive therapy was very, very effective"},{"time":321000,"text":"in the treatment of depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"And of course, in those days, there were no antidepressant drugs,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and it became very, very popular."},{"time":329000,"text":"They would anesthetize people,"},{"time":331000,"text":"convulse them, but the real difficulty was"},{"time":334000,"text":"that there was no way to paralyze muscles."},{"time":336000,"text":"So people would have a real grand mal seizure."},{"time":339000,"text":"Bones were broken. Especially in old, fragile people,"},{"time":342000,"text":"you couldn't use it."},{"time":344000,"text":"And then in the 1950s, late 1950s, the so-called muscle relaxants"},{"time":349000,"text":"were developed by pharmacologists,"},{"time":351000,"text":"and it got so that you could induce a complete convulsion,"},{"time":355000,"text":"an electroencephalographic convulsion -- you could see it on the brain waves --"},{"time":358000,"text":"without causing any convulsion in the body except a little bit of twitching of the toes."},{"time":363000,"text":"So again, it was very, very popular and very, very useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"Well, you know, in the middle '60s,"},{"time":371000,"text":"the first antidepressants came out. Tofranil was the first."},{"time":375000,"text":"In the late '70s, early '80s, there were others,"},{"time":379000,"text":"and they were very effective."},{"time":380000,"text":"And patients' rights groups seemed to get very upset"},{"time":383000,"text":"about the kinds of things that they would witness."},{"time":386000,"text":"And so the whole idea of electroconvulsive, electroshock therapy disappeared,"},{"time":392000,"text":"but has had a renaissance in the last 10 years."},{"time":396000,"text":"And the reason that it has had a renaissance"},{"time":399000,"text":"is that probably about 10 percent of the people, severe depressives,"},{"time":405000,"text":"do not respond, regardless of what is done for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"Now, why am I telling you this story at this meeting?"},{"time":414000,"text":"I'm telling you this story, because actually ever since"},{"time":417000,"text":"Richard called me and asked me to talk about"},{"time":419000,"text":"-- as he asked all of his speakers --"},{"time":421000,"text":"to talk about something that would be new to this audience,"},{"time":424000,"text":"that we had never talked about, never written about,"},{"time":427000,"text":"I've been planning this moment."},{"time":430000,"text":"This reason really is that I am a man who, almost 30 years ago,"},{"time":435000,"text":"had his life saved by two long courses of electroshock therapy."},{"time":443000,"text":"And let me tell you this story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"I was, in the 1960s, in a marriage. To use the word bad"},{"time":453000,"text":"would be perhaps the understatement of the year."},{"time":456000,"text":"It was dreadful."},{"time":458000,"text":"There are, I'm sure, enough divorced people in this room"},{"time":461000,"text":"to know about the hostility, the anger, who knows what."},{"time":467000,"text":"Being someone who had had a very difficult childhood,"},{"time":472000,"text":"a very difficult adolescence --"},{"time":473000,"text":"it had to do with not quite poverty but close."},{"time":477000,"text":"It had to do with being brought up in a family where no one spoke English,"},{"time":480000,"text":"no one could read or write English."},{"time":482000,"text":"It had to do with death and disease and lots of other things."},{"time":486000,"text":"I was a little prone to depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"So, as things got worse, as we really began to hate each other,"},{"time":492000,"text":"I became progressively depressed over a period of a couple of years,"},{"time":496000,"text":"trying to save this marriage,"},{"time":498000,"text":"which was inevitably not to be saved."},{"time":502000,"text":"Finally, I would schedule -- all my major surgical cases,"},{"time":508000,"text":"I was scheduling them for 12, one o'clock in the afternoon,"},{"time":512000,"text":"because I couldn't get out of bed before about 11 o'clock."},{"time":516000,"text":"And anybody who's been depressed here knows what that's like."},{"time":519000,"text":"I couldn't even pull the covers off myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"Well, you're in a university medical center,"},{"time":525000,"text":"where everybody knows everybody, and it's perfectly clear to my colleagues,"},{"time":528000,"text":"so my referrals began to decrease."},{"time":530000,"text":"As my referrals began to decrease,"},{"time":533000,"text":"I clearly became increasingly depressed"},{"time":537000,"text":"until I thought, my God, I can't work anymore."},{"time":539000,"text":"And, in fact, it didn't make any difference"},{"time":541000,"text":"because I didn't have any patients anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543000,"text":"So, with the advice of my physician,"},{"time":547000,"text":"I had myself admitted to the acute care psychiatric unit of our university hospital."},{"time":552000,"text":"And my colleagues, who had known me since medical school"},{"time":555000,"text":"in that place, said, \"Don't worry, chap. Six weeks,"},{"time":557000,"text":"you're back in the operating room. Everything's going to be great.\""},{"time":561000,"text":"Well, you know what bovine stercus is?"},{"time":565000,"text":"That proved to be a lot of bovine stercus."},{"time":571000,"text":"I know some people who got tenure in that place with lies like that."},{"time":576000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":582000,"text":"So I was one of their failures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"But it wasn't that simple. Because by the time"},{"time":587000,"text":"I got out of that unit, I was not functional at all."},{"time":592000,"text":"I could hardly see five feet in front of myself."},{"time":594000,"text":"I shuffled when I walked. I was bowed over."},{"time":597000,"text":"I rarely bathed. I sometimes didn't shave. It was dreadful."},{"time":602000,"text":"And it was clear -- not to me,"},{"time":605000,"text":"because nothing was clear to me at that time anymore --"},{"time":608000,"text":"that I would need long-term hospitalization"},{"time":612000,"text":"in that awful place called a mental hospital."},{"time":616000,"text":"So I was admitted, in 1973, in the spring of 1973,"},{"time":622000,"text":"to the Institute of Living, which used to be called the Hartford Retreat."},{"time":625000,"text":"It was founded in the eighteenth century,"},{"time":627000,"text":"the largest psychiatric hospital in the state of"},{"time":631000,"text":"Connecticut, other than the huge public hospitals"},{"time":633000,"text":"that existed at that time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"And they tried everything they had."},{"time":637000,"text":"They tried the usual psychotherapy."},{"time":639000,"text":"They tried every medication available in those days."},{"time":642000,"text":"And they did have Tofranil and other things -- Mellaril, who knows what."},{"time":646000,"text":"Nothing happened except that I got jaundiced from one of these things."},{"time":650000,"text":"And finally, because I was well known in Connecticut,"},{"time":656000,"text":"they decided they better have a meeting of the senior staff."},{"time":660000,"text":"All the senior staff got together, and I later found out what happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"They put all their heads together and they decided"},{"time":670000,"text":"that there was nothing that could be done"},{"time":672000,"text":"for this surgeon who had essentially separated himself from the world,"},{"time":676000,"text":"who by that time had become so overwhelmed,"},{"time":680000,"text":"not just with depression and feelings"},{"time":683000,"text":"of worthlessness and inadequacy,"},{"time":685000,"text":"but with obsessional thinking,"},{"time":688000,"text":"obsessional thinking about coincidences."},{"time":690000,"text":"And there were particular numbers that every time I saw them,"},{"time":693000,"text":"just got me dreadfully upset -- all kinds of ritualistic observances,"},{"time":699000,"text":"just awful, awful stuff."},{"time":701000,"text":"Remember when you were a kid, and you had to step on every line?"},{"time":704000,"text":"Well, I was a grown man who had all of these rituals,"},{"time":708000,"text":"and it got so there was a throbbing, there was a ferocious fear in my head."},{"time":712000,"text":"You've seen this painting by Edvard Munch,"},{"time":714000,"text":"The Scream. Every moment was a scream."},{"time":719000,"text":"It was impossible. So they decided there was no therapy,"},{"time":722000,"text":"there was no treatment. But there was one treatment,"},{"time":725000,"text":"which actually had been pioneered at the Hartford hospital in the early 1940s,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and you can imagine what it was. It was pre-frontal lobotomy."},{"time":738000,"text":"So they decided -- I didn't know this, again,"},{"time":740000,"text":"I found this out later --"},{"time":741000,"text":"that the only thing that could be done was"},{"time":743000,"text":"for this 43-year-old man to have a pre-frontal"},{"time":747000,"text":"lobotomy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Well, as in all hospitals, there was a resident"},{"time":753000,"text":"assigned to my case. He was 27 years old,"},{"time":756000,"text":"and he would meet with me two or three times a week."},{"time":758000,"text":"And of course, I had been there, what, three or four months at the time."},{"time":762000,"text":"And he asked to meet with the senior staff, and they agreed to meet with him"},{"time":765000,"text":"because he was very well thought of in that place."},{"time":767000,"text":"They thought he had a really extraordinary future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"And he dug in his heels and said,"},{"time":772000,"text":"\"No. I know this man better than any of you. I have met with him over and over again."},{"time":776000,"text":"You've just seen him from time to time. You've read reports and so forth."},{"time":780000,"text":"I really honestly believe that the basic problem here is pure depression,"},{"time":785000,"text":"and all of the obsessional thinking comes out of it."},{"time":788000,"text":"And you know, of course, what'll happen if you do a pre-frontal lobotomy."},{"time":791000,"text":"Any of the results along the spectrum,"},{"time":795000,"text":"from pretty bad to terrible, terrible, terrible"},{"time":797000,"text":"is going to happen. If he does the best he can,"},{"time":801000,"text":"he will have no further obsessions,"},{"time":803000,"text":"probably no depression, but his affect will be dulled,"},{"time":806000,"text":"he will never go back to surgery,"},{"time":808000,"text":"he will never be the loving father that he was to his two children,"},{"time":812000,"text":"his life will be changed. If he has the usual result,"},{"time":815000,"text":"he will end up like 'One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest.'"},{"time":818000,"text":"And you know about that, just essentially in a stupor the rest of his life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"Well, he said, \"Can't we try a course of electroshock therapy?\""},{"time":829000,"text":"And you know why they agreed? They agreed to humor him."},{"time":832000,"text":"They just thought, \"Well, we'll give a course of 10."},{"time":836000,"text":"And so we'll lose a little time. Big deal. It doesn't make any difference.\""},{"time":840000,"text":"So they gave the course of 10,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and the first -- the usual course, incidentally, was six to eight"},{"time":845000,"text":"and still is six to eight."},{"time":847000,"text":"Plugged me into the wires, put me to sleep, gave me the muscle relaxant."},{"time":851000,"text":"Six didn't work. Seven didn't work."},{"time":853000,"text":"Eight didn't work. At nine, I noticed --"},{"time":856000,"text":"and it's wonderful that I could notice anything"},{"time":859000,"text":"-- I noticed a change. And at 10, I noticed a real change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863000,"text":"And he went back to them, and they agreed to do another 10."},{"time":866000,"text":"Again, not a single one of them"},{"time":868000,"text":"-- I think there are about seven or eight of them --"},{"time":870000,"text":"thought this would do any good. They thought this was a temporary change."},{"time":872000,"text":"But, lo and behold, by 16, by 17,"},{"time":876000,"text":"there were demonstrable differences in the way I felt."},{"time":880000,"text":"By 18 and 19, I was sleeping through the night."},{"time":883000,"text":"And by 20, I had the sense, I really had the sense"},{"time":887000,"text":"that I could overcome this,"},{"time":890000,"text":"that I was now strong enough that by an act of will,"},{"time":893000,"text":"I could blow the obsessional thinking away."},{"time":895000,"text":"I could blow the depression away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"And I've never forgotten -- I never will forget"},{"time":901000,"text":"-- standing in the kitchen of the unit,"},{"time":904000,"text":"it was a Sunday morning in January of 1974,"},{"time":908000,"text":"standing in the kitchen by myself and thinking, \"I've got the strength now to do this.\""},{"time":914000,"text":"It was as though those tightly coiled wires in my head had been disconnected"},{"time":919000,"text":"and I could think clearly."},{"time":921000,"text":"But I need a formula. I need some thing to say to myself"},{"time":926000,"text":"when I begin thinking obsessionally, obsessively."},{"time":930000,"text":"Well, the Gilbert and Sullivan fans in this room"},{"time":935000,"text":"will remember \"Ruddigore,\" and they will remember Mad Margaret,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and they will remember that she was married"},{"time":940000,"text":"to a fellow named Sir Despard Murgatroyd."},{"time":944000,"text":"And she used to go nuts, every five minutes or so in the play,"},{"time":948000,"text":"and he said to her, \"We must have a word to bring you back to reality,"},{"time":951000,"text":"and the word, my dear, will be 'Basingstoke.'\""},{"time":955000,"text":"So every time she got a little nuts,"},{"time":957000,"text":"he would say, \"Basingstoke!\" And she would say,"},{"time":959000,"text":"\"Basingstoke, it is.\" And she would be fine for a little while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963000,"text":"Well, you know, I'm from the Bronx. I can't say \"Basingstoke.\""},{"time":967000,"text":"But I had something better. And it was very simple."},{"time":971000,"text":"It was, \"Ah, fuck it!\""},{"time":974000,"text":"(Laughter) Much better than \"Basingstoke,\""},{"time":979000,"text":"at least for me. And it worked -- my God, it worked."},{"time":983000,"text":"Every time I would begin thinking obsessionally --"},{"time":985000,"text":"again, once more, after 20 shock treatments"},{"time":989000,"text":"-- I would say, \"Ah, fuck it.\""},{"time":993000,"text":"And things got better and better,"},{"time":995000,"text":"and within three or four months,"},{"time":998000,"text":"I was discharged from that hospital, and I joined a group of surgeons"},{"time":1001000,"text":"where I could work with other people in the community,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"not in New Haven, but fairly close by."},{"time":1008000,"text":"I stayed there for three years."},{"time":1010000,"text":"At the end of three years, I went back to New Haven,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"had remarried by that time."},{"time":1018000,"text":"I brought my wife with me, actually, to make sure I could get through this."},{"time":1024000,"text":"My children came back to live with us."},{"time":1030000,"text":"We had two more children after that."},{"time":1033000,"text":"Resuscitated the career, even better than it had been before."},{"time":1038000,"text":"Went right back into the university"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and began to write books."},{"time":1045000,"text":"Well, you know, it's been a wonderful life."},{"time":1048000,"text":"It's been, as I said, close to 30 years."},{"time":1052000,"text":"I stopped doing surgery about six years ago"},{"time":1055000,"text":"and became a full-time writer, as many people know."},{"time":1059000,"text":"But it's been very exciting. It's been very happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062000,"text":"Every once in a while, I have to say, \"Ah, fuck it.\""},{"time":1064000,"text":"Every once in a while, I get somewhat depressed and a little obsessional."},{"time":1067000,"text":"So, I'm not free of all of this. But it's worked. It's always worked."},{"time":1077000,"text":"Why have I chosen, after never, ever talking about this, to talk about it now?"},{"time":1085000,"text":"Well, those of you who know some of these books"},{"time":1088000,"text":"know that one is about death and dying,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"one is about the human body and the human spirit,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"one is about the way mystical thoughts are constantly in our minds,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"and they have always to do with my own personal experiences."},{"time":1103000,"text":"One might think reading these books"},{"time":1106000,"text":"-- and I've gotten thousands of letters about them"},{"time":1109000,"text":"by people who do think this --"},{"time":1111000,"text":"that based on my life's history as I've portrayed in the books,"},{"time":1114000,"text":"my early life's history, I am someone who has overcome adversity."},{"time":1119000,"text":"That I am someone who has drunk, drank, drunk"},{"time":1124000,"text":"of the bitter dregs of near-disaster in childhood"},{"time":1131000,"text":"and emerged not just unscathed but strengthened."},{"time":1136000,"text":"I really have it figured out, so that I can advise people about"},{"time":1139000,"text":"death and dying, so that I can talk about mysticism and the human spirit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1144000,"text":"And I've always felt guilty about that."},{"time":1146000,"text":"I've always felt that somehow I was an impostor"},{"time":1149000,"text":"because my readers don't know what I have just told you."},{"time":1154000,"text":"It's known by some people in New Haven, obviously,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"but it is not generally known."},{"time":1159000,"text":"So one of the reasons that I have come here to talk about this today"},{"time":1164000,"text":"is to -- frankly, selfishly --"},{"time":1169000,"text":"unburden myself and let it be known"},{"time":1172000,"text":"that this is not an untroubled mind that has written all of these books."},{"time":1178000,"text":"But more importantly, I think,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"is the fact that a very significant proportion"},{"time":1183000,"text":"of people in this audience are under 30,"},{"time":1187000,"text":"and there are many, of course, who are well over 30."},{"time":1193000,"text":"For people under 30, and it looks to me like almost all of you"},{"time":1196000,"text":"-- I would say all of you --"},{"time":1197000,"text":"are either on the cusp of a magnificent and exciting career"},{"time":1202000,"text":"or right into a magnificent and exciting career:"},{"time":1206000,"text":"anything can happen to you. Things change."},{"time":1210000,"text":"Accidents happen. Something from childhood comes back to haunt you."},{"time":1214000,"text":"You can be thrown off the track."},{"time":1216000,"text":"I hope it happens to none of you,"},{"time":1217000,"text":"but it will probably happen to a small percentage of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1222000,"text":"To those to whom it doesn't happen, there will be adversities."},{"time":1227000,"text":"If I, with the bleakness of spirit,"},{"time":1231000,"text":"with no spirit, that I had in the 1970s"},{"time":1236000,"text":"and no possibility of recovery,"},{"time":1238000,"text":"as far as that group of very experienced psychiatrists thought,"},{"time":1242000,"text":"if I can find my way back from this,"},{"time":1244000,"text":"believe me, anybody can find their way back"},{"time":1248000,"text":"from any adversity that exists in their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1253000,"text":"And for those who are older, who have lived through"},{"time":1254000,"text":"perhaps not something as bad as this,"},{"time":1257000,"text":"but who have lived through difficult times,"},{"time":1260000,"text":"perhaps where they lost everything, as I did,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"and started out all over again, some of these things will seem very familiar."},{"time":1269000,"text":"There is recovery."},{"time":1274000,"text":"There is redemption. And there is resurrection."},{"time":1282000,"text":"There are resurrection themes in every society that has ever been studied,"},{"time":1286000,"text":"and it is because not just only do we fantasize"},{"time":1289000,"text":"about the possibility of resurrection and recovery,"},{"time":1292000,"text":"but it actually happens. And it happens a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1296000,"text":"Perhaps the most popular resurrection theme,"},{"time":1300000,"text":"outside of specifically religious ones,"},{"time":1303000,"text":"is the one about the phoenix, the ancient story of the phoenix,"},{"time":1307000,"text":"who, every 500 years, resurrects itself from its own ashes"},{"time":1314000,"text":"to go on to live a life that is"},{"time":1317000,"text":"even more beautiful than it was before. Richard,"},{"time":1320000,"text":"thanks very much."}]}]}